Kurds Warn of Danger to Security at Turkey Poll, Milliyet Says

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-05-06T05:42:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/kurds-warn-of-danger-to-security-at-turkey-poll-milliyet-says.html
Pro-Kurdish politicians and non-
government groups warned that military operations in the
southeast and political moves against Kurds endangered security
at June’s parliamentary election, Milliyet said.  The Turkish authorities are not allowing Kurds to freely
express their opinions and conditions to hold general elections
in the southeast will “disappear,” according to a joint
statement made by the Democratic Society Congress at a meeting
in the city of Diyarbakir.  Kurds will seek their rights in events that may resemble
campaigns for democracy in Egypt and  Syria , said Aysel Tugluk,
who is an independent pro-Kurdish lawmaker in  Turkey ’s
parliament.      Aysel Tuglak, a pro-Kurdish politician in parliament, warned of
